"klirlxastati" is not strictly a type-3 fu'ivla, it should be "klirnxastati".
The rule is use -r-, if you can't then use -n-, if you can't then use -l-.
So -l- would be used only as a last resort, between r and n or between n and r.

But why not follow the pattern and call it something-kliru? The name "astatine" 
comes from Greek αστατος astatos, meaning "unsteady", so how about "nalstokliru"?

